<FIRST>u a AM-BabyBeaten     01-30 0226</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Baby Beaten,0231</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Say Baby Beaten By Two Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 14-month-old girl was hospitalized with a
skull fracture and stab wounds after two boys, ages 4 and 5,
attacked her with a screwdriver, a shovel, a hammer and a brick,
police said Sunday.
   The girl was in critical but stable condition at Cardinal Glennon
Children's Hospital, a nursing supervisor said.
   The girl lost a lot of blood in the attack Saturday, in which she
was stabbed in the face, an ear and the back of her head,
authorities said.
   Authorities did not release the names of either the victim or the
two boys, who are brothers. One of the boys told authorities they
had assaulted the girl ``because she was ugly; we liked doing it.''
   The girl was being cared for by her mother's boyfriend while her
mother was being held at the St. Louis County Adult Correctional
Institution awaiting trial on charges of felony theft and
misdemeanor assault, police said. The mother has been in jail since
Dec. 23.
   The girl was assaulted early Saturday afternoon in the basement
of her south St. Louis home. Several children and adults were
upstairs at the time, police said. The boys and some family members
were visiting the home.
   The Missouri Division of Family Services will conduct a further
investigation, police said.
