<HEAD>British Revelers in Night of `Silly Horseplay'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. MORITZ, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British revelers invaded a luxury
resort hotel and hauled off paintings and other objects in a night
of ``silly horseplay'' that drew banner headlines Monday in the
nation's leading tabloid.
   The Blick newspaper said 50 to 60 jeering partygoers entered the
hotel lobby Saturday night to the wail of bagpipes and ``tried to
take away everything that wasn't nailed down.''
