<HEAD>Don Johnson Plays Real-Life Cop, Nabs Intruder in Hotel Room</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In true ``Miami Vice'' fashion, actor Don
Johnson nabbed an intruder in a hotel room as the man rifled through
the purse of his fiancee, actress Melanie Griffith, police said
Monday.
   Johnson, 39, who portrays a hard-nosed but flashily dressed
undercover cop on the TV series, discovered the intruder when he and
Miss Griffith opened the door to their room at the Hotel Bel-Air on
Sunday night, said police Capt. Clayton Mayes.
