<HEAD>Cocker Spaniel Named Top Dog</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cocker spaniels are the nation's favorite dog for
the sixth year in a row, while Labrador retrievers have edged out
poodles for the No. 2 spot, the American Kennel Club said Monday.
   The annual best-friend census, based on the number of dogs
registered among each breed by AKC, ranks poodles, second in 1987,
at No. 3 for 1988.
   They're followed by golden retrievers, German shepherds and chow
chows _ the latter three unchanged from 1987.
   Rottweilers moved from No. 12 to seventh, while beagles fell one
position to No. 8. Dachshunds were unchanged at No. 9 while
miniature schnauzers slipped two rungs to 10th place.
