<TEXT>
   The operators of a church youth camp and
the families of four teen-agers who drowned in a 1987 flooding
accident settled three negligence lawsuits Monday.
   Terms of the deal reached in Kerrville, where the civil lawsuits
totaling $11 million were being heard, were not released.
   The families of John Bankston Jr. and Leslie Gossett, plus
sisters Stacey Smith and Tonya Smith, had filed the lawsuits.
