<HEAD>Guerrillas Ambush Troop Truck, 10 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communist guerrillas ambushed a truck
carrying government troops and a civilian guide, killing 10 people
and wounding five, a military report said Tuesday.
   The soldiers were responding to a kidnapping report when their
truck hit a landmine Sunday morning in Roxas, about 150 miles
southeast of Manila, the report said.
   Seven constabulary soldiers, two policemen and guide Leonilda
Mapalad died in the attack by New People's Army rebels in San Rafael
village, the report added.
   Lt. Felixberto Castillo, who led the troops, and four others were
wounded in the incident. A constable was also missing and believed
taken hostage by the attackers, the report said.
   The rebels fled with 12 M-16 and M-14 rifles and a grenade
launcher taken from the slain troops, the report said.
   In another incident, five people were killed in a grenade blast
Monday on the southern island of Mindanao, the military said.
   Businessman Roberto Ihaon, his wife and three of their children
were killed when a grenade was thrown into their house in Ozamis
City while they were eating supper. Three other children were
seriously wounded, Lt. Col. Teofisto Salcedo reported.
   The motive and identity of the attackers was not immediately
known.
