<FIRST>a e BC-WKD--HomeVideo Adv00   01-30 0461</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-WKD--Home Video, Adv 00,0487</SECOND>
<HEAD>$Adv00</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Anytime</HEAD>
<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>Video View: Home Video Reviews</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SCOTT WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   Videos reviewed this week: ``Defense of the Realm,'' ``Monkey
Shines.''
   
   ``Defense of the Realm'' (Nelson Home Entertainment. VHS-Beta.
Rated R)
   
   Like ``The Whistleblower,'' an equally tidy little thriller,
``Defense of the Realm'' is long on atmosphere. It's worth the
rental if only to see how a Another Western Democracy has its own
dirty obsessions with state secrets.
   Gabriel Byrne plays the reporter who tumbles to the Big Story
after an old sot of a colleague (Denholm Elliott) stumbles onto it
first and dies mysteriously, apparently for a secret the shadow
government thinks is worth killing him to protect.
   It's effective to see the young reporter start to pull at the
ends of the story until a strand works loose, then put the strands
of the story together until finally ...
   Ah, but that would be telling, eh?
   Some might fault the movie's abrupt ending, but let's admonish
these curmudgeonly souls with the old '60s epigram: ``It ain't
paranoia if they really are out to get you.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   ``Monkey Shines'' (Orion Home Video. VHS-Beta. Rated R)
   
   ``There's something ... unnatural about you and that monkey!''
   Yup, that line actually is uttered in this amazingly unscary yawn
by ``Night of the Living Dead'' writer-director George Romero.
   Of course, the female monkey has been getting secret injections
from a crazed, high-foreheaded medical researcher who wants to
augment her mental abilities.
   And of course, the embittered, paralyzed law student meets a
gorgeous physical therapist with a trapeze. Whoa, time for some
sexual frustration here! Aw, you knew that was coming, didn't you?
   But the hopped-up monkey has assumed an eerie doppelganger
relationship with her master. And she's jealous. Uh-oh! ... Cue the
scary music ... Put the camera on a handtruck and run it around on
the floor! Get the physical therapist in the rack! Get her up on
that trapeze! TASTEFULLY!!!
   Of course there's that inevitable and none-too-suspenseful
showdown between man and beast. But you knew that, eh?
   Will the good guy win and get the gorgeous physical therapist?
And how will he get her down off that trapeze? Will he ever ``walk''
again?
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Motion Picture Association of America rating definitions:
   G _ General audiences. All ages admitted.
   PG _ Parental guidance suggested. Some material may not be
suitable for children.
   PG-13 _ Special parental guidance strongly suggested for children
under 13. Some material may be inappropriate for young children.
   R _ Restricted. Under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult
guardian.
   X _ No one under 17 admitted. Some states may have higher age
restrictions.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Release Anytime</NOTE>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
