<HEAD>Dollar Firms, Stock Prices Decline Moderately In Early Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar firmed in early trading after
opening lower against the Japanese yen Tuesday. Stock prices fell
moderately.
   The dollar opened trading at 129.59 yen, down 0.14 yen from
Monday's close of 129.73 yen, but began edging higher.
   A dealer at the Bank of Tokyo said the dollar could rise above
the 130-yen level in the near future. During Monday's dealings, it
moved briefly to 130.03 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which lost 111.57 points Monday, shed another 45.19
points, or 0.14 percent, in the first 15 minutes of trading to move
to 31,522.31.
